<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species has been identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cavanillesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea cavanillesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cairica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. cairica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has nothing to do with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cairica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. cairica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and from the structure of the sepals and the leaf shape, it is probably closest to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eggersiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea eggersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
